definitions.definition: An arrow in a category ; ( less formally ) an abstraction that generalises a map from one mathematical object to another and is structure-preserving in a way that depends on the branch of mathematics from which it arises.
Being or having distinct variants of a plant or animal species in the same locale; polymorphism .

main_definition: ( mathematics , category theory ) ( formally ) An arrow in a category ; ( less formally ) an abstraction that generalises a map from one mathematical object to another and is structure-preserving in a way that depends on the branch of mathematics from which it arises.
secondary_definitions: ( biology ) Being or having distinct variants of a plant or animal species in the same locale; polymorphism .
